Rating: 4
Loved this! I stirred in some of the cheddar into the potato mixture along with some ricotta cheese. Used dried herbs and heavy cream instead of whole milk. After adding the cheddar to the top I drizzled a little butter and sprinkled on a thin layer of panko. Also, used pancetta instead of regular bacon. D-E-L-I-C-I-O-U-S!!!!!!!

Rating: 4
Vegetarians, I substituted two tablespoons of butter and a cup of sliced mushrooms for the bacon. Also substituted buttermilk for the whole milk, since I had it on hand. Yummy way to use up leftover mashed potatoes.

Rating: 4
Excellent! Easy to make. Used turkey pastrami instead of bacon since that is what I had. Can be made ahead and then just placed in oven to heat.

Rating: 3
I discovered the recipe searching for a way to use up leftovers. It was an sutstanding way to use leftover mashed potatoes. I had to use dry herbs to avoid a trip to the store but they made the potatoes taste wonderful. I will plan for this dish next time I make it and use fresh herbs instead. My family loves a nice crunch with dishes that have been topped with cheese so I sprinkled it with panko bread crumbs before baking and toasted the crumbs in the broiler before serving. It was a hit.

Rating: 3
This was a great way to use leftovers and give them new life. My family loved the shallot flavor and it was a big hit. Will make this one again for sure!

